.com/check-name-pm-jan-arogya-yojana-final-beneficiaries-list-mera-pmjay-gov/) can be checked by calling the helpline number at 14555 or by visiting the official \u201cAm I Eligible\u201d portal at mera.pmjay.gov.in.", "006-normal": "Till date, there is yet no official notification regarding the online registration / applications for Ayushman Bharat Yojana. However, after the cabinet meeting held last month in which it gives approval for [Ayushman Bharat \u2013 National Health Protection Mission (AB-NHPM)](https://sarkariyojana.com/ayushman-bharat-national-health-protection-mission-ab-nhpm/), it is expected that the applications will start soon. Now Ayushman Bharat Yojana Beneficiaries can also avail [PMJAY services through Common Service Centers (CSCs)](https://sarkariyojana.com/ayushman-bharat-yojana-beneficiaries-registration-csc-common-service-centers/)."}, "002-section": {"000-title": "Apply Online for Ayushman Bharat Yojana", "001-normal": "There is no need to apply online or offline for Ayushman Bharat Yojana, it is an eligibility based scheme. There are no online application forms or registration being made for the scheme."}, "003-section": {"000-title": "Ayushman Bharat Yojana Eligibility Criteria / Beneficiary Selection", "001-normal": "The eligibility criteria of Ayushman Bharat Yojana is solely based on the Socio-Economic Caste Census (SECC) data covering both rural and urban areas across the country. The total number of the beneficiary families would be about 10.74 Crore consisting of deprived rural families and identified occupational category of urban workers\u2019 families.", "002-normal": "However, if the criteria of exclusion / inclusion / deprivation / occupation in SECC data is changed in future, the scheme will take into account all the changes and the beneficiary families will be included / excluded on the basis of same changed criteria. See [Ayushman Bharat Yojana List of Beneficiaries](https://sarkariyojana.com/ayushman-bharat-yojana-list-of-beneficiaries/)  \n \u2014 Also see the [Process of Identification of PMRSSM Beneficiaries](https://www.pmjay.gov.in/sites/default/files/2018-07/GuidelinesonProcessofBeneficiaryIdentification_0.pdf)"}, "004-section": {"000-title": "Ayushman Bharat Yojana Coverage / Implementation", "001-normal": "The National Health Protection Scheme / Mission under the Ayushman Bharat scheme will be implemented in all the states and union territories to cover all the targeted beneficiary families across the country. The programme will be implemented by the Ayushman Bharat National Health Protection Mission Agency (AB-NHPMA) under the supervision of Ministry of Health and Family Welfare, Government of India.", "002-normal": "State Health Agency (SHA), newly formed or formed using an existing trust / society / no-profit company / state nodal agency would be responsible for the implementation of the scheme in respective state & UT\u2019s.", "003-normal": "**List of Hospitals**  \n The cashless benefits of treatment under the scheme would be available in all the government hospitals and empaneled private hospitals except the negative list across the country.", "004-normal": "**\u0939\u093f\u0902\u0926\u0940 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092a\u095d\u0947\u0902:** [\u0906\u092f\u0941\u0937\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0928 \u092d\u093e\u0930\u0924 \u092f\u094b\u091c\u0928\u093e \u0915\u0940 \u092a\u0942\u0930\u0940 \u091c\u093e\u0928\u0915\u093e\u0930\u0940](https://sarkariyojana.com/ayushman-bharat-yojana-online-application-forms/)"}, "005-section": {"000-title": "Ayushman Bharat Programme \u2013 Salient Features", "001-normal": "Below are some of the main / salient features of Ayushman Bharat Programme", "002-listElement": "- National Health Protection Mission and Health & Wellness Centers are the two major initiatives started under the Ayushman Bharat Scheme.", "003-listElement": "- National Health Protection Mission will provide insurance coverage of up to Rs. 5 Lakh per family per year for secondary and tertiary care hospitalization.", "004-listElement": "- 1.5 Lakh health and wellness centers would be started in health centers / hospitals across the country. More than 18 thousands already in operation.", "005-listElement": "- About 10 Crore deprived rural and urban families (About 40% of the total population of the country) to be covered under the health insurance coverage scheme.", "006-listElement": "- The selection of beneficiaries to be done on the basis of SECC data.", "007-listElement": "- There will be no restriction on the size of the covered beneficiary family.", "008-listElement": "- The scheme will lead to timely treatment of the patient and increase in overall patient satisfaction. Overall efficiency and productivity of health care services will be improved thus improving the quality of life.", "009-listElement": "- The premium of the insurance coverage will be completely borne by the central and state governments based on the ration defined by the Ministry of Finance.", "010-listElement": "- State Health Agency (SHA) would be the responsible body for the implementation of the scheme in states.", "011-listElement": "- The cost of the treatments would be defined by the government in the advance as packages to control the cost.", "012-listElement": "- The benefits of the scheme would be portable across the country, meaning, a beneficiary can avail the cashless treatment at any government or empaneled private hospital in the country.", "013-listElement": "- To enable the paperless & cashless transaction, central government would establish a robust, modular, scalable and interoperable IT platform in partnership with NITI Aayog.", "014-listElement": "- Ayushman Bharat \u2013 National Health Protection Mission will subsume the on-going centrally sponsored schemes \u2013 Rashtriya Swasthya Bima Yojana (RSBY) and the Senior Citizen Health Insurance Scheme (SCHIS).", "015-normal": "Check the complete [Ayushman Bharat Yojana (PMJAY) Claim Settlement Guidelines](https://www.pmjay.gov.in/sites/default/files/2018-07/GuidelinesonClaimSettlement_0.pdf)"}, "006-section": {"000-title": "Quick Facts & Information about Ayushman Bharat", "001-table": {"row": 20, "column": 2, "data": [["Data Point", "Fact / Information"], ["Name of Scheme / Initiative", "Ayushman Bharat Scheme"], ["Launched", "14th April, 2018 by Prime Minister Narendra Modi"], ["Initiatives Under the Scheme", "1. National Health Protection Mission  \n 2. Health & Wellness Centers"], ["Implementing Authority", "Ayushman Bharat National Health Protection Mission Agency (AB-NHPMA) under Ministry of Health and Family Welfare, Government of India"], ["Scheme Coverage", "All states and Union Territories"], ["Budget Allocation", "Rs. 1200 Crore in 2018-19 Union Budget"], ["**1. National Health Protection Mission**"], ["No. of Beneficiaries", "More than 10 Crore Families Under National Health Protection Mission Initiative"], ["Benefits", "[Health insurance coverage](https://sarkariyojana.com/national-health-protection-scheme-nhps-health-insurance-cover-poor/) of up to Rs. 5 Lakh per annum per family for secondary & tertiary care hospitalization"], ["Selection of Beneficiaries", "Deprived rural & identified occupational category of urban workers\u2019 families as per [SECC-2011 data](https://sarkariyojana.com/download-bpl-list-pm-ujjwala-yojana-secc-2011-data/)"], ["Size of covered beneficiary family", "No restriction on family size"], ["Insurance premium", "Entire cost of premium to be borne by central & state governments"], ["Treatment avalibility", "At all government & empaneled private hospitals"], ["**2. Health and Wellness Centers**"], ["What?", "Health & wellness centers to provide basic health services / diagnostics & basic drugs for free."], ["Facilities", "Point of care for diagnostics / hub & spoke, wellness rooms for Yoga, Physiotherapy & group meetings, separate consulting space, free drug dispensation, telemedicine facilities, storage space for drugs & consumables and waiting area for 30+ people"], ["No. of centers", "1.5 Lakh total number to be started, more than 18000 already in operation"], ["Beneficiaries", "All citizens of the country"], ["More details", "[Ayushman Bharat Health & Wellness Centers](https://sarkariyojana.com/health-wellness-centres-services-ayushman-bharat-yojana-2018/)"]]}, "002-normal": "More details about the Ayushman Bharat \u2013 National Health Protection Mission such as list of hospitals, list of beneficiaries is available on the official website at pmjay.gov.in."}, "007-section": {"000-title": "References", "001-normal": "For all other details, visit the official website pmjay.gov.in", "002-normal": "**Also Read** \u2013 [Ayushman Family Cards for Health Insurance under PMRSSM](https://sarkariyojana.com/ayushman-family-cards-health-insurance-pmrssm-modicare/)"}}